RACE.RACE_TEXT: THISTLEDOWN RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 22400. FOR ACCREDITED OHIO FOALS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 4 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 4 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NAMBITI never far back, rallied four wide through the turn and upper stretch under right handed urging, was put to a strong hand ride through the late stages and got up in the final strides in the seven path. TIGER TRAIL had good early speed along the inside, shifted out to the three path nearing the half mile pole, moved up two wide through the turn, altered course to the middle of the racetrack, dug in determinedly late and just missed. BABA LOOEY chased the pace three then two wide into the stretch, made the lead, set the balance of the pace and was outfinished in the final yards. OHIO EAGLE forwardly placed in the three path. checked when in tight as TIGER TRAIL shifted out to the three path near the half mile marker, dropped back then came on again late two wide. NEBULOSA away alertly, set the pace along the inside to the top of the stretch then weakened. JACK BE FAST failed to menace. TIDE RISING was no factor. THE RIDER OF OHIO EAGLE LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF TIGER TRAIL FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE NEAR THE HALF MILE POLE. AFTER REVIEW THE STEWARDS UPHELD THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
